    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_12948773" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/12948773" />
    <a title="jeremy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/635936-jeremy"><img alt="jeremy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1569705896p2/635936.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/12948773?book_show_action=true">Jan 20, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="jeremy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="jeremy" href="/user/show/635936-jeremy">jeremy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781586480493" href="/book/show/850315.War_Is_A_Force_That_Gives_Us_Meaning">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/635936-jeremy?shelf=gen-nonfiction">gen-nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/635936-jeremy?shelf=politics">politics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer12948773" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9908944299488986013">&quot;the whole truth may finally be too hard to utter, but the process of healing only begins when we are able to at least acknowledge the tragedy and accept our share of the blame.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText9908944299488986013" style="display:none">"the whole truth may finally be too hard to utter, but the process of healing only begins when we are able to at least acknowledge the tragedy and accept our share of the blame."</span>
