    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_77534734" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/77534734" />
    <a title="John" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2095414-john"><img alt="John" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1317221772p2/2095414.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/77534734?book_show_action=true">Nov 12, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John" href="/user/show/2095414-john">John</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781586480493" href="/book/show/850315.War_Is_A_Force_That_Gives_Us_Meaning">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2095414-john?shelf=2009">2009</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer77534734" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17827058728336925212">Hedges spent two decades as a war correspondent before writing this anti-war book. He doesn&apos;t call himself a pacifist, but has found it difficult to find any good in war. He saw the wars in El Salvador, Serbia, Angola, and more. In this book he writes of the common denominators in all of them. War corrupts even the best of people, turning them into bloodthirsty savages. But worse, it unleashes criminals and gives them moral cover for their wickedness. War leaves absolute destruction in its wake,</span>
  <span id="freeText17827058728336925212" style="display:none">Hedges spent two decades as a war correspondent before writing this anti-war book. He doesn't call himself a pacifist, but has found it difficult to find any good in war. He saw the wars in El Salvador, Serbia, Angola, and more. In this book he writes of the common denominators in all of them. War corrupts even the best of people, turning them into bloodthirsty savages. But worse, it unleashes criminals and gives them moral cover for their wickedness. War leaves absolute destruction in its wake, both physical and spiritual. <br /><br />It is difficult, if not impossible to recognize any benefit in war whatever. Any good that comes of war, is just as likely to have resulted through peaceful means, and untold wickedness is often the result of even the best intentions. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17827058728336925212" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


